# Cursor rules — My SvelteKit Starter

Detailed source of truth: **AGENTS.md** at the repo root.

## Trigger: external design → code (read before editing files)

If the user (or context) mentions **Stitch**, **Lovable**, **visual parity**, **pixel perfect**, **match the design**, **exported HTML/CSS**, **Figma / prototype** as the main reference, or **DESIGN_TO_CURSOR**:

1. **Open and follow** **`DESIGN_TO_CURSOR.md`** at the repo root (read it fully with the read tool if it is not in context).
2. Then apply **AGENTS.md** (component catalog, i18n, `npm run check`).
3. Map the design to **Button, Card, Section**, etc.; tune tokens in **`src/app.css`** and **`src/lib/styles/stitch-m3.css`**; do not leave only raw HTML without migrating to components.

If none of that applies, follow **AGENTS.md** as usual.

---

Short **Stitch / Lovable → visual parity** flow: checklist and prompt in **DESIGN_TO_CURSOR.md**.

If the user asks to clone an external design: map to catalog components, adjust tokens in `app.css` / `stitch-m3.css`, avoid layout-only loose HTML.

## Golden rule

**Do not write raw HTML** (`<button>`, `<h1>`, hand-built cards) if a component already exists under `src/lib/components/ui/` or `src/lib/components/`.

## Quick catalog (current imports)

| Use | Import |
|-----|--------|
| Button (shadcn variants) | `$lib/components/ui/button` |
| Card / CardHeader / CardTitle… | `$lib/components/ui/card` |
| Dialog | `$lib/components/ui/dialog` |
| Input, Textarea, Label | `$lib/components/ui/input`, `textarea`, `label` |
| Skeleton, Spinner | `$lib/components/ui/skeleton`, `spinner` |
| Sonner toasts | `$lib/components/ui/sonner` → `<Toaster />` in layout |
| Marketing layout | `Container`, `Section`, `Heading`, `Text`, `Grid` in `$lib/components/ui/*.svelte` |
| Blocks | `HeroSection`, `FeaturesSection` in `$lib/components/ui/` |
| Project | `Footer`, `CopyButton`, `Newsletter`, `AiPrompt`, `JsonLd`, `CookieConsent`, `BlogLayout`, `LoadingBlock`, `LiveChat`, `Analytics` in `$lib/components/` |

**Not** present as legacy paths: `ThemeToggle.svelte`, `Modal.svelte`, loose `Button.svelte` at the root of `ui/`.

## Utilities

```ts
import { toast } from '$lib/stores/toast';
// Layout: <Toaster /> (Sonner) + <ToastContainer /> for the store

import { mode, toggleMode } from 'mode-watcher';

import { t, locale, setLocale } from '$lib/i18n/index';

import { setSeo } from '$lib/seo';

import { reveal } from '$lib/reveal';

import { cn } from '$lib/utils';

import { clickOutside } from '$lib/actions/clickOutside';
```

## Stack

- **Svelte 5** — runes: `$state`, `$props`, `$derived`, `$effect`
- **SvelteKit 2** — routes, `load`, form actions
- **TypeScript**
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — utilities in components; tokens in `src/app.css` and `src/lib/styles/stitch-m3.css`
- **shadcn-svelte + bits-ui** — patterns under `src/lib/components/ui/`

## Props (Svelte 5)

Type like this (no generic on `$props()`):

```ts
let { title }: { title: string } = $props();
```

Use snippets instead of slots: `{@render children?.()}`

## Customization

- `src/lib/site-config.ts` — name, URL, social
- `src/lib/i18n/es.json` and `en.json` — layout (`layout.*`) and home (`home.*`) copy
- `src/lib/seo.ts` — `setSeo`, `$seo` store

## New page / component

See **AGENTS.md**: `+page.svelte`, `setSeo`, optional `+page.ts` / `+page.server.ts`; no `async` in the `.svelte` file.

## AEO (Markdown twins) — aplicar siempre

En cada página indexable, sin que el usuario lo pida:

1. Entrada en `src/lib/site-pages.ts` + `setSeo` en `$effect` con `$locale`.
2. `buildXxxMarkdown` en `src/lib/aeo/builders/` + registro en `src/lib/aeo/registry.ts`.
3. Ruta `src/routes/<slug>.md/+server.ts` con `serveMarkdownTwin` (home → `index.md`).
4. Copy del twin desde **i18n** (`tFor`), no HTML-to-Markdown.

Infra ya cableada: `hooks.server.ts` (content negotiation), `<link rel="alternate" type="text/markdown">` en layout. Detalle: **AGENTS.md** → SEO + GEO + AEO.

## shadcn-svelte CLI

```bash
npx shadcn-svelte@latest add <component>
```
